- The file also does not include any routing registration (Route::get, Route::post, Route::resource, attributes, or route annotations) or any literal path constants. While Laravel supports controller naming conventions for resource routes (e.g., Route::resource maps create/store to specific HTTP paths), the resource name (the path prefix) is not present in this file. Because the instructions require that paths be extracted only from literal strings in the source code or from naming conventions explicitly present in the code, I did not infer or guess any paths.
- For these reasons I produced an empty list: there are no API entries whose paths can be determined from literal strings or explicit conventions within this file. If you provide the project's route files (e.g., routes/web.php or routes/api.php) or other files that register this controller with a path, I can extract concrete API entries from those.
